Big audience but I wonder whether calling it Blues means an older audience.  Also caught Chris Gumbley playing Cannonball Adderley tunes at Hotel du Vin, great playing from a top quintet.  Lianne La Havas was brilliant at Big Top; artists like her and Laura Mvula belong in a jazz festival in my view

I remember seeing him at the Jazz Festival several years ago with Gregory Porter singing Gran Torino, with the lyrics written on a piece of paper! Have seen him many times since and he always puts on an exceptional show.
